01:03:29,472 --> 01:03:31,473
Hmm, me too.

992
01:03:34,060 --> 01:03:35,977
You weren't in the state legislature.

993
01:03:41,776 --> 01:03:43,985
Hi, I'm Ellen Mitchell.

994
01:03:45,112 --> 01:03:46,154
Who are you?

995
01:03:52,119 --> 01:03:54,538
Look, I'll make this easy on you.

996
01:03:55,248 --> 01:03:57,749
I never see him anymore.

997
01:03:59,001 --> 01:04:01,503
I barely know him anymore.

998
01:04:02,880 --> 01:04:05,465
I'd just kind of like
to know where he is.

999
01:04:11,639 --> 01:04:14,182
This could get me into a lot of trouble.

1000
01:04:41,544 --> 01:04:43,378
Open it, please, Duane.

1001
01:04:53,681 --> 01:04:54,890
Oh, my God.

1002
01:04:55,057 --> 01:04:56,850
I'm sorry, you're not allowed in here.

1003
01:04:57,018 --> 01:05:00,645
- Mr. Alexander left strict instructions.
STEVENSON: - I'll explain it to you later.

1004
01:05:04,442 --> 01:05:05,859
Oh, no.

1005
01:05:33,179 --> 01:05:34,846
What happened?

1006
01:05:35,932 --> 01:05:36,973
It was a stroke.

1007
01:05:38,392 --> 01:05:40,310
It's pretty bad.

1008
01:05:45,107 --> 01:05:47,108
I don't understand.

1009
01:05:48,402 --> 01:05:50,320
Is he going to...?

1010
01:05:52,573 --> 01:05:54,032
I'm sorry.

1011
01:06:13,177 --> 01:06:14,886
You're leaving?

1012
01:06:15,846 --> 01:06:18,473
I'm not the first lady anymore.

1013
01:06:19,266 --> 01:06:21,226
I shouldn't be here.

1014
01:06:21,394 --> 01:06:23,186
Where are you going?

1015
01:06:23,729 --> 01:06:24,980
[SIGHS

1016
01:06:28,109 --> 01:06:29,526
Home.

1017
01:06:30,736 --> 01:06:32,320
DAVE:
Where's home?

1018
01:06:34,031 --> 01:06:35,907
ELLEN:
Look, can we stop with the 20 questions?

1019
01:06:36,075 --> 01:06:38,618
Because I'm really not in the mood.

1020
01:06:47,378 --> 01:06:49,504
Souvenirs. Towels and stuff.

1021
01:06:50,548 --> 01:06:52,424
You're leaving too?

1022
01:06:55,886 --> 01:06:58,221
I never wanted to hurt anybody.

1023
01:06:58,806 --> 01:07:01,474
Heck, I even thought I was helping.

1024
01:07:06,439 --> 01:07:07,689
[WHIMPERING]

1025
01:07:23,789 --> 01:07:25,582
You know...

1026
01:07:25,750 --> 01:07:28,793
...you make this little
deal with yourself that...

1027
01:07:28,961 --> 01:07:31,629
...you can put up with
all the other women...

1028
01:07:31,797 --> 01:07:34,340
...and you can even do without a life.

1029
01:07:36,677 --> 01:07:38,970
You can even do without children...

1030
01:07:40,347 --> 01:07:43,349
...because you believe
in what you're doing and you think....

1031
01:07:45,853 --> 01:07:48,563
You thought you had a chance
to help people.

1032
01:07:55,321 --> 01:07:56,905
How are you gonna get home?

1033
01:07:58,949 --> 01:07:59,991
ELLEN:
Um....

1034
01:08:00,159 --> 01:08:02,535
[CHUCKLES]

1035
01:08:02,703 --> 01:08:05,163
I don't know. I hadn't really...

1036
01:08:05,331 --> 01:08:07,332
...thought it out that far.

1037
01:08:10,544 --> 01:08:13,088
ELLEN:
Are you sure this goes somewhere?

1038
01:08:13,255 --> 01:08:16,091
They say LBJ used it all the time.

1039
01:08:17,968 --> 01:08:19,010
[BELL BUZZES]

1040
01:08:55,756 --> 01:08:58,925
DAVE: Duane said he'd leave
a car right over there.

1041
01:09:04,098 --> 01:09:06,474
When did you, uh, first know?

1042
01:09:06,642 --> 01:09:08,434
I mean, about me?

1043
01:09:10,437 --> 01:09:12,272
In the car, I think.

1044
01:09:12,898 --> 01:09:16,025
On the way to the shelter,
you looked at my legs.

1045
01:09:18,404 --> 01:09:20,238
Bill stopped looking a long time ago.

1046
01:09:22,783 --> 01:09:25,243
I thought maybe it was in the shower, heh.

1047
01:09:27,746 --> 01:09:28,788
No.

1048
01:09:37,339 --> 01:09:39,174
[POLICE SIREN WAILS]

1049
01:09:41,635 --> 01:09:43,219
Oh, my God.

1050
01:09:43,846 --> 01:09:45,763
- What?
- Police.

1051
01:09:51,478 --> 01:09:53,229
- What'd you do?
- I don't know.

1052
01:10:01,906 --> 01:10:04,240
POLICEMAN: See your driver's license, sir?
DAVE: Here, sir.

1053
01:10:05,367 --> 01:10:06,409
And registration.

1054
01:10:07,828 --> 01:10:11,956
- Um....
- No, uh, I, uh, must've left it at home.

1055
01:10:13,000 --> 01:10:14,459
Step out of the car, please.

1056
01:10:17,838 --> 01:10:20,173
- Both of us?
- Yes, both of you, please.

1057
01:10:27,765 --> 01:10:29,098
Well, you may not be aware...

1058
01:10:29,266 --> 01:10:32,810
...but there is a posted "No left turn"
sign just down the block here.

1059
01:10:32,978 --> 01:10:34,437
You went right through it.

1060
01:10:34,605 --> 01:10:36,814
DAVE:
Oh.

1061
01:10:36,982 --> 01:10:39,484
- I don't know what I was thinking.
- Oh, my gosh.

1062
01:10:40,569 --> 01:10:41,945
Oh.

1063
01:10:42,112 --> 01:10:43,780
We're look-alikes.

1064
01:10:44,198 --> 01:10:46,199
Heh, we don't look like
each other, but I mean...

1065
01:10:46,367 --> 01:10:50,245
I know what you think. People hire us to
impersonate the president and first lady.

1066
01:10:50,412 --> 01:10:52,747
- We work out of an agency.
- You sure look like him.

1067
01:10:52,915 --> 01:10:55,375
Thanks. We work very hard at it.
I mean, uh, she....

1068
01:10:55,542 --> 01:10:58,086
She got her hair cut to look...
Perfect match.

1069
01:10:58,254 --> 01:11:01,256
We just, uh, played the Sapperstein wedding.
They loved us.

1070
01:11:01,423 --> 01:11:04,259
We did.... We did our, uh,
Club Med routine...

1071
01:11:04,426 --> 01:11:08,346
...where the first lady and the president
go to Club Med, and there's Bill Mitchell.

1072
01:11:08,514 --> 01:11:11,683
He's like, "At 0700,
I want an hour of volleyball.

1073
01:11:11,850 --> 01:11:15,979
And then at 0830, I want a complete
briefing on the whole surf situation."

1074
01:11:16,146 --> 01:11:20,316
And then the big finale
at, uh, the Talent Club.

1075
01:11:20,484 --> 01:11:22,944
[SINGING]
The sun will come out tomorrow

1076
01:11:23,112 --> 01:11:25,446
Bet your bottom dollar that tomorrow

1077
01:11:25,614 --> 01:11:26,698
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
I'm okay.

1078
01:11:26,865 --> 01:11:31,494
[SINGING] There'll be sun
Just thinkin' about tomorrow

1079
01:11:31,662 --> 01:11:34,289
Clears away the cobwebs.
And the sorrow

1080
01:11:34,456 --> 01:11:37,917
Till there's none tomorrow.

1081
01:11:38,085 --> 01:11:44,549
[SINGING] Tomorrow, I love you
Tomorrow, it's only a day away

1082
01:11:44,717 --> 01:11:45,842
[DAVE SCATS]

1083
01:11:46,010 --> 01:11:51,222
[BOTH SINGING]
Tomorrow, tomorrow, we love you, tomorrow

1084
01:11:51,390 --> 01:11:57,562
You are only a day away

1085
01:11:57,730 --> 01:11:59,397
[CROWD APPLAUDING ]

1086
01:11:59,732 --> 01:12:03,609
Thank you. Thanks.
We haven't worked out the final harmony.

1087
01:12:03,777 --> 01:12:05,862
- This is a full-time job?
- Uh, yeah, lately.

1088
01:12:06,030 --> 01:12:08,448
Lately, it's been, uh, pretty much full-time.

1089
01:12:08,615 --> 01:12:11,951
Mr. and Mrs. Kovic,
I'm not gonna give you a ticket.

1090
01:12:12,119 --> 01:12:13,328
You're not?

1091
01:12:13,495 --> 01:12:16,664
I think you ought to save
all the money you have.

1092
01:12:16,832 --> 01:12:17,874
[CHUCKLES]

1093
01:12:18,042 --> 01:12:19,500
- Not gonna give a ticket.
- Right.

1094
01:12:19,668 --> 01:12:21,169
- Says we should save.
- Thank you.

1095
01:12:21,337 --> 01:12:23,546
Thanks. That's very funny, heh.

1096
01:12:23,714 --> 01:12:25,381
- Listen, you're very good.
- Right.

1097
01:12:25,549 --> 01:12:29,302
- But she needs a lot of work.
DAVE: - Yes, I know. She's kind of new at it.

1098
01:12:29,470 --> 01:12:30,511
Now, you drive safely, huh?

1099
01:12:30,679 --> 01:12:33,556
Thank you. Thank you, officer.
Thank you very much.

1100
01:12:33,807 --> 01:12:35,391
Okay.

1101
01:12:46,320 --> 01:12:48,237
Uh, I'm not sure I'm this hungry.

1102
01:12:48,405 --> 01:12:51,866
Wait.
This is a very special sandwich.

1103
01:12:58,832 --> 01:13:00,333
This is good.

1104
01:13:00,501 --> 01:13:01,542
What's in it?

1105
01:13:02,628 --> 01:13:03,669
That's a secret.

1106
01:13:06,924 --> 01:13:08,925
ELLEN:
You have a lot of secrets.

1107
01:13:09,093 --> 01:13:10,635
DAVE:
I guess.

1108
01:13:19,353 --> 01:13:22,355
So, what do you do the rest of the time?

1109
01:13:22,773 --> 01:13:24,440
You mean,
when I'm not running the country?

1110
01:13:24,608 --> 01:13:26,234
Mm-hm.

1111
01:13:26,777 --> 01:13:30,613
I run a temp agency.
You know, secretaries and stuff.

1112
01:13:31,281 --> 01:13:33,991
- You mean, you find people jobs?
- Yes.

1113
01:13:34,493 --> 01:13:35,701
ELLEN:
Hmm.

1114
01:13:35,869 --> 01:13:37,453
Is that funny?

1115
01:13:38,038 --> 01:13:40,331
It's just more than most people
do around here.

1116
01:13:40,499 --> 01:13:41,624
[SCOFFS]

1117
01:13:41,792 --> 01:13:44,544
Don't get carried away.
I'm not that good at it.

1118
01:13:44,795 --> 01:13:46,295
And your family?

1119
01:13:46,463 --> 01:13:48,798
I mean, I assume you're married.

1120
01:13:50,384 --> 01:13:51,884
I was.

1121
01:13:52,052 --> 01:13:53,594
Once.

1122
01:13:54,930 --> 01:13:55,972
It didn't take.

1123
01:14:04,398 --> 01:14:05,982
You know, Dave...

1124
01:14:06,150 --> 01:14:08,234
It is Dave, isn't it?

1125
01:14:10,487 --> 01:14:12,321
I can't keep all of this a secret.

1126
01:14:13,490 --> 01:14:15,199
Yeah, I know.

1127
01:14:17,828 --> 01:14:19,871
I liked doing it though.

1128
01:14:21,206 --> 01:14:24,417
I mean, not the fancy stuff
with all the helicopters...

1129
01:14:24,585 --> 01:14:26,752
...and the TV cameras...

1130
01:14:28,589 --> 01:14:30,840
...but I liked saving that shelter.

1131
01:14:31,925 --> 01:14:35,178
I liked helping people
that I hadn't even met before.

1132
01:14:37,764 --> 01:14:40,808
Just then, I felt like I wasn't
pretending anymore.

1133
01:14:44,229 --> 01:14:46,272
I don't think you were pretending.

1134
01:14:57,618 --> 01:15:00,620
What would you do if
you were still in there?

1135
01:15:03,165 --> 01:15:06,876
I mean, if you had one more chance
to be president...

1136
01:15:07,294 --> 01:15:09,420
...what would you do then?

1137
01:15:19,598 --> 01:15:21,390
Lots of things.

1138
01:15:40,369 --> 01:15:43,120
Excuse me. You can't stop here.

1139
01:15:43,288 --> 01:15:45,623
Look, there's no visitors at...

1140
01:15:47,417 --> 01:15:49,293
- Hi.
MAN: - Mr. President?

1141
01:15:53,131 --> 01:15:57,301
- I'm sorry, sir, I didn't realize that...
- Just getting a little fresh air.

1142
01:15:57,469 --> 01:15:59,095
MAN:
Certainly, sir.

1143
01:15:59,263 --> 01:16:01,764
I was wondering, if you don't mind,
how did you get...?

1144
01:16:01,932 --> 01:16:04,308
The president wanted some ice cream.

1145
01:16:31,003 --> 01:16:34,046
You make a nice president, Dave Kovic.

1146
01:16:34,464 --> 01:16:36,048
Thanks.

1147
01:16:39,219 --> 01:16:40,845
See you.

1148
01:16:54,776 --> 01:16:57,153
WOMAN: We are delighted you're visiting
the White House.

1149
01:16:57,321 --> 01:16:59,530
Let's keep moving, folks. We're walking.

1150
01:16:59,698 --> 01:17:02,408
A million visitors go through
the White House every year...

1151
01:17:02,576 --> 01:17:05,328
...making it the most frequently
toured home in the country.

1152
01:17:05,495 --> 01:17:07,830
We're walking, we're walking
and we're stopping.

1153
01:17:07,998 --> 01:17:10,499
Whatever changes
from one administration to the next...

1154
01:17:10,667 --> 01:17:12,960
...the White House always maintains
its dignity.

1155
01:17:13,128 --> 01:17:14,253
We're walking.

1156
01:17:14,421 --> 01:17:17,632
He's walking. He's Bob Alexander,
our White House chief of staff.

1157
01:17:17,799 --> 01:17:19,008
I can't believe it!

1158
01:17:19,176 --> 01:17:21,594
What an honor, really, for all of you.
We're walking.

1159
01:17:21,762 --> 01:17:25,097
Forty-two presidents and their wives
have lived in the White House.

1160
01:17:30,854 --> 01:17:34,482
I had nothing to do with this.
He called it himself. I swear to God.

1161
01:17:44,785 --> 01:17:46,827
What do you think you're doing?

1162
01:17:47,621 --> 01:17:49,288
You mean, the press conference?

1163
01:17:49,456 --> 01:17:52,750
I, uh, have a couple of ideas I wanted
to share with the country.

1164
01:17:54,044 --> 01:17:57,421
Share?

1165
01:17:57,756 --> 01:17:59,632
You don't call a press conference.

1166
01:17:59,800 --> 01:18:02,176
I call a press conference.

1167
01:18:02,552 --> 01:18:04,970
You're nothing. Do you understand?

1168
01:18:05,555 --> 01:18:06,931
You're nobody.

1169
01:18:07,099 --> 01:18:08,891
I'm not nobody.

1170
01:18:09,059 --> 01:18:10,768
You're lint!

1171
01:18:10,936 --> 01:18:12,687
You're a flea!

1172
01:18:13,146 --> 01:18:15,314
You're a blip!

1173
01:18:16,483 --> 01:18:18,025
Well...

1174
01:18:18,235 --> 01:18:19,944
...maybe I am.

1175
01:18:21,154 --> 01:18:22,363
But you're fired.

1176
01:18:24,491 --> 01:18:25,533
What?

1177
01:18:26,243 --> 01:18:28,911
I said you're fired. Go on, get out of here.

1178
01:18:29,079 --> 01:18:31,288
- Oh, I'm fired?
- Yup.

1179
01:18:31,456 --> 01:18:32,998
You're fired.

1180
01:18:35,168 --> 01:18:37,169
- Fine.
- Fine?

1181
01:18:37,838 --> 01:18:39,422
Fine.

1182
01:18:40,757 --> 01:18:42,967
The whole press corps is right out there.

1183
01:18:43,135 --> 01:18:45,928
Should I go tell them?
Or did you want to?

1184
01:18:46,096 --> 01:18:47,304
[DOOR OPENS

1185
01:18:47,472 --> 01:18:52,309
Darling, they're waiting in the Press Room.
I really think you ought to get in there.

1186
01:18:52,561 --> 01:18:53,686
Oh.

1187
01:18:53,854 --> 01:18:55,396
Bob.

1188
01:18:55,564 --> 01:18:58,607
I'm sorry. I thought we were alone.

1189
01:19:07,367 --> 01:19:10,786
I'd like your resignation on my
desk by the time I get back.

1190
01:19:17,794 --> 01:19:20,171
Don't touch anything on that desk.

1191
01:19:20,964 --> 01:19:22,298
- How are you?
- How you doing?

1192
01:19:22,466 --> 01:19:23,799
Hi.

1193
01:19:23,967 --> 01:19:26,135
- Hey, guys. What's up?
- It's the vice-president.

1194
01:19:26,303 --> 01:19:28,220
- What could it be?
- The ex-vice-president.

1195
01:19:28,388 --> 01:19:31,390
He'll be a prison reformer
in Denver in a year.

1196
01:19:31,892 --> 01:19:34,059
ALAN:
Okay, they're coming. Let's go.

1197
01:19:40,317 --> 01:19:41,859
Good luck.

1198
01:19:42,611 --> 01:19:44,528
[CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING

1199
01:19:50,243 --> 01:19:52,995
Thanks for coming on such short notice.

1200
01:19:53,163 --> 01:19:54,455
I, uh....

1201
01:19:56,041 --> 01:20:00,169
I'd like to begin with an
announcement that, uh...

1202
01:20:03,340 --> 01:20:04,465
I've, uh...

1203
01:20:05,091 --> 01:20:08,219
...asked Bob Alexander to resign
as White House chief of staff.

1204
01:20:08,386 --> 01:20:10,721
[REPORTERS CHATTERING INDISTICTLY]

1205
01:20:11,932 --> 01:20:15,935
Over the last few months, Bob and I
have come to believe in different things.

1206
01:20:16,686 --> 01:20:21,774
He thinks this country's fine and we
should go about doing business as usual.

1207
01:20:24,277 --> 01:20:26,320
I just don't feel that way.

1208
01:20:27,364 --> 01:20:28,989
Not anymore.

1209
01:20:29,866 --> 01:20:32,409
Because, hey, things aren't fine.

1210
01:20:32,577 --> 01:20:36,205
We've got so many problems, that we
don't even want to look at them anymore.

1211
01:20:36,373 --> 01:20:39,542
They just blend together
into this great, big noise...

1212
01:20:39,709 --> 01:20:42,628
...and pretty soon we can't even
hear ourselves think.

1213
01:20:42,796 --> 01:20:45,172
But that's not even the worst part.

1214
01:20:45,340 --> 01:20:47,049
The worst part is that we....

1215
01:20:47,759 --> 01:20:50,427
We feel we can't do anything about it.

1216
01:20:51,972 --> 01:20:53,806
And that's a tragedy...

1217
01:20:54,516 --> 01:20:55,558
...because we can.

1218
01:20:59,104 --> 01:21:02,606
But we don't know where to start.
Maybe that's what it is.

1219
01:21:03,316 --> 01:21:05,109
But I have an idea...

1220
01:21:05,277 --> 01:21:07,236
...of where we can start.

1221
01:21:10,240 --> 01:21:12,199
From today...

1222
01:21:13,618 --> 01:21:16,787
...I'm gonna make it the responsibility
of this government...

1223
01:21:16,955 --> 01:21:19,707
...to find a job for every American
who wants one.

1224
01:21:19,875 --> 01:21:21,625
[CHATTERING INDISTICTLY]

1225
01:21:24,379 --> 01:21:27,715
Have you ever seen the
look on somebody's face...

1226
01:21:27,883 --> 01:21:30,551
...the day that they finally get a job?

1227
01:21:31,261 --> 01:21:33,554
I've had some experience with this.

1228
01:21:34,139 --> 01:21:36,181
They look like they could fly.

1229
01:21:36,433 --> 01:21:40,853
And it's not about the paycheck. It's about
respect. It's about looking in the mirror...

1230
01:21:41,021 --> 01:21:44,356
...and knowing that you've done
something valuable with your day.

1231
01:21:44,649 --> 01:21:48,569
And if one person could start to feel
that way, and then another person...

1232
01:21:48,737 --> 01:21:53,282
...then pretty soon all these other
problems we're facing may not seem so...

1233
01:21:53,450 --> 01:21:55,242
...impossible.

1234
01:22:01,958 --> 01:22:04,835
You don't really know how
much you can do until you...

1235
01:22:05,003 --> 01:22:07,463
...stand up and decide to try.

1236
01:22:17,223 --> 01:22:19,642
That's it. So let's get to work.
Thank you.

1237
01:22:19,809 --> 01:22:21,185
ALL:
Mr. President.

1238
01:22:22,896 --> 01:22:24,480
Thank you, Mr. President.

1239
01:22:24,648 --> 01:22:27,983
In the boldest initiative yet of the
new Bill Mitchell administration...

1240
01:22:28,151 --> 01:22:31,862
...the president has proposed a
comprehensive full employment program...

1241
01:22:32,030 --> 01:22:34,949
...unparalleled since the days of FDR.

1242
01:22:35,116 --> 01:22:38,953
The proposal brought swift
reaction, here on Capitol Hill.

1243
01:22:39,120 --> 01:22:44,041
President Mitchell's right. Putting people
to work is what we ought to be doing.

1244
01:22:44,209 --> 01:22:46,752
Better to have a job
than collecting a welfare check.

1245
01:22:46,920 --> 01:22:51,173
We're here trying to carry the water for him.
I've carried water.

1246
01:22:51,341 --> 01:22:54,134
And then now to say this.
This guy's out to lunch.

1247
01:22:54,302 --> 01:22:56,553
He's, you know.... Somebody's...

1248
01:22:56,721 --> 01:22:58,889
The lights are on, but nobody's home.

1249
01:22:59,057 --> 01:23:03,268
I love it. It's great.
All we've gotta do is cut Star Wars.

1250
01:23:03,436 --> 01:23:07,356
I want to look at Mitchell's proposal.

1251
01:23:07,524 --> 01:23:11,360
Like the program I presented
when I ran for president.

1252
01:23:11,528 --> 01:23:14,905
Has the president taken leave of his
faculties? I ask you, Eleanor Clift.

1253
01:23:15,073 --> 01:23:17,199
This is the definition
of modern leadership.

1254
01:23:17,367 --> 01:23:20,536
Set out a bold goal and you don't
say how you're going to get there.

1255
01:23:20,704 --> 01:23:23,038
They tried this in Russia
and wrecked the country.

1256
01:23:23,206 --> 01:23:25,124
I wonder if the Communists got him.

1257
01:23:25,291 --> 01:23:27,668
If you look at a
photograph of Bill Mitchell...

1258
01:23:27,836 --> 01:23:30,254
...taken before the stroke
and one right after...

1259
01:23:30,422 --> 01:23:32,715
LARRY: - What?
- ...you will see distinct differences.

1260
01:23:32,882 --> 01:23:34,800
Are you saying this is a conspiracy?

1261
01:23:34,968 --> 01:23:37,344
Yes, I am saying this is a conspiracy.

1262
01:23:37,512 --> 01:23:39,346
Do you think you're a little paranoid?

1263
01:23:39,514 --> 01:23:42,057
No. Have you compared the photographs,
Larry?

1264
01:23:55,321 --> 01:23:56,947
[ELLEN HUMMING "TOMORROW"]

1265
01:24:05,290 --> 01:24:08,250
Pfft, this is crazy.

1266
01:24:11,588 --> 01:24:14,423
The U.S .News hammered us,
but they're always tough on that.

1267
01:24:14,591 --> 01:24:16,884
- Rosenthal loved us in The Times.
- Oh, that's good.

1268
01:24:17,052 --> 01:24:19,553
RANDI: Mr. President,
Mr. Nance is waiting for you inside.

1269
01:24:19,721 --> 01:24:21,430
- Ah. Who?
- The vice-president.

1270
01:24:21,598 --> 01:24:24,224
[BOTH WHISPERING]

1271
01:24:24,392 --> 01:24:26,685
- The vice-president.
- Oh, the...

1272
01:24:26,853 --> 01:24:28,896
Nance. I thought...

1273
01:24:29,064 --> 01:24:31,940
Uh, get my, uh, I want my ears checked.
Would you do that?

1274
01:24:32,108 --> 01:24:35,152
Sorry, I didn't understand.
Ever since the stroke I get a little...

1275
01:24:35,320 --> 01:24:36,862
[MUTTERS]

1276
01:24:37,030 --> 01:24:38,697
Oh, my God.

1277
01:25:00,261 --> 01:25:02,137
Mr. President...

1278
01:25:03,556 --> 01:25:05,808
- ...these are a gift from the King of Togo.
- Oh.

1279
01:25:05,975 --> 01:25:07,893
- Fertility beads.
- Ah.

1280
01:25:08,061 --> 01:25:11,230
These are from the people of Burundi.

1281
01:25:11,397 --> 01:25:12,564
Oh.

1282
01:25:13,691 --> 01:25:14,733
Thank you.

1283
01:25:14,901 --> 01:25:17,069
They know hats in Burundi. Look at this.

1284
01:25:20,448 --> 01:25:22,825
Mr. President,
may I speak frankly with you?

1285
01:25:22,992 --> 01:25:25,786
Yes, please. Sit down.
It's good to see you.

1286
01:25:29,582 --> 01:25:33,293
I know we haven't always gotten along.
I know we've disagreed politically.

1287
01:25:33,461 --> 01:25:37,172
And I suppose I know
what you think of me personally.

1288
01:25:38,550 --> 01:25:41,969
But I've always tried to respect
the role you wanted me to play.

1289
01:25:43,096 --> 01:25:46,765
When I've disagreed with this
administration, I've kept it to myself.

1290
01:25:48,434 --> 01:25:51,103
When you wanted my support,
you always had it.

1291
01:25:51,271 --> 01:25:52,771
Yes.

1292
01:25:52,939 --> 01:25:54,231
Damn it, Bill.

1293
01:25:54,399 --> 01:25:57,151
How could you do
something like this to me?

1294
01:25:59,195 --> 01:26:02,322
- Do what?
- Come on, we're not children.

1295
01:26:02,490 --> 01:26:06,118
I didn't have anything to do with this
First Liberty nonsense and you know it.

1296
01:26:07,287 --> 01:26:11,039
- First Liberty.
- All I've got is my integrity, Bill.

1297
01:26:11,207 --> 01:26:12,541
Okay?

1298
01:26:13,418 --> 01:26:15,252
That's all I have left.

1299
01:26:15,420 --> 01:26:18,213
Now, I don't know why you've turned
your attack dogs on me.

1300
01:26:18,381 --> 01:26:21,008
- They're not my attack dogs.
- What?

1301
01:26:22,177 --> 01:26:23,552
I'll take care of this.

1302
01:26:23,887 --> 01:26:26,346
- We made it up.
- What do you mean, you made it up?

1303
01:26:26,514 --> 01:26:29,308
Well, we had to, Dave.
The guy's a Boy Scout.

1304
01:26:29,475 --> 01:26:31,351
DAVE:
But, Alan, this is wrong.

1305
01:26:31,519 --> 01:26:33,103
Wrong?

1306
01:26:33,271 --> 01:26:36,940
Oh, I know. It looks awfully bad
and I'm really embarrassed...

1307
01:26:37,108 --> 01:26:38,275
...but it was Bob's idea.

1308
01:26:44,199 --> 01:26:45,866
[REPORTERS CHATTERING INDISTICTLY]

1309
01:26:47,619 --> 01:26:50,204
MAN:
Have you spoken to the president?

1310
01:27:01,049 --> 01:27:03,342
When I first began to
look into the allegations...

1311
01:27:03,509 --> 01:27:06,595
...concerning First Liberty Savings
and Loan...

1312
01:27:06,763 --> 01:27:10,891
...I thought the wrongdoing
was restricted to the vice-president's office.

1313
01:27:11,809 --> 01:27:14,144
I think you better take a look at this.

1314
01:27:16,231 --> 01:27:21,026
But as I began to investigate,
I realized that this pattern of corruption...

1315
01:27:21,194 --> 01:27:23,445
...extended much higher.

1316
01:27:24,030 --> 01:27:28,242
I was saddened to discover at least
15 separate acts of intervention...

1317
01:27:28,409 --> 01:27:30,827
...by this administration...

1318
01:27:30,995 --> 01:27:35,374
...most with the full knowledge of
the president, and all of them illegal.

1319
01:27:35,541 --> 01:27:39,419
- Jesus Christ.
- Federal regulators were influenced...

1320
01:27:39,587 --> 01:27:41,546
...records were destroyed...

1321
01:27:41,714 --> 01:27:43,507
...and pressure was brought to bear...

1322
01:27:47,595 --> 01:27:50,013
...by President Mitchell himself.

1323
01:27:50,181 --> 01:27:53,016
- Now he's making stuff up about me.
- He's not.

1324
01:27:55,937 --> 01:27:57,729
He's not?

1325
01:27:59,941 --> 01:28:01,108
You mean, I did all that?

1326
01:28:01,276 --> 01:28:03,860
You didn't.
Bill Mitchell did.

1327
01:28:13,079 --> 01:28:16,290
This is a mistake.
We shouldn't be doing this right now.

1328
01:28:16,457 --> 01:28:17,958
I can't go into hiding.

1329
01:28:18,584 --> 01:28:20,210
[REPORTERS CHATTERING INDISTICTLY]

1330
01:28:22,171 --> 01:28:23,380
WOMAN 1:
What are you hiding?

1331
01:28:27,969 --> 01:28:30,929
MAN 1: Mr. President,
what did you know and when did you know it?

1332
01:28:33,766 --> 01:28:36,143
MAN 2:
When will you have a confession?

1333
01:28:36,936 --> 01:28:38,729
MAN 3:
Will you answer these allegations?

1334
01:28:38,896 --> 01:28:40,731
WOMAN 2:
When will you make a statement?

1335
01:28:40,898 --> 01:28:42,983
Is this job stuffjust a smoke screen?

1336
01:28:43,151 --> 01:28:46,153
MAN 4:
Mr. President, did you commit the crime?

1337
01:28:46,946 --> 01:28:51,450
Mr. President, I don't know any other way
to put it. This dog just won't hunt.

1338
01:28:51,617 --> 01:28:55,329
We may be able to hold off on this
First Liberty thing for a little while...

1339
01:28:55,496 --> 01:28:58,123
...but if you've been running around
with this new jobs...

1340
01:28:58,291 --> 01:29:00,375
Just put us on a spit
and bring in the sauce.

1341
01:29:00,543 --> 01:29:03,170
- If you could just wait for a couple months.
- Yeah, wait.

1342
01:29:03,338 --> 01:29:05,047
- Yeah.
DAVE: - No.

1343
01:29:05,214 --> 01:29:07,174
No, I don't want to wait a while.
We can't.

1344
01:29:07,342 --> 01:29:09,926
MAN: Mr. President,
I understand how you feel...

1345
01:29:10,094 --> 01:29:12,888
...but we're talking about
obstructing federal regulators...

1346
01:29:13,056 --> 01:29:15,015
...violating election laws.

1347
01:29:15,475 --> 01:29:18,518
I got people up on the Hill
talking impeachment.

1348
01:29:18,686 --> 01:29:21,104
What is with President
Mitchell lately, huh?

1349
01:29:21,272 --> 01:29:25,776
I know the president's supposed to serve
four years, but now it may be 15 to 20.

1350
01:29:25,943 --> 01:29:27,694
[AUDIENCE LAUGHING AND APPLAUDING

1351
01:29:27,862 --> 01:29:31,948
But we make fun of the president. We
knock the president. But it's a tough job.

1352
01:29:32,116 --> 01:29:36,578
[ON TV] Take today. The president woke up,
broke the law, got caught, he pardoned himself.

1353
01:29:36,746 --> 01:29:38,121
That is a full day.

1354
01:29:38,289 --> 01:29:40,082
[AUDIENCE LAUGHING AND APPLAUDING
ON TV]

1355
01:29:40,249 --> 01:29:43,710
- Oh, and now political action groups...
- Mr. President.

1356
01:29:43,878 --> 01:29:45,504
- May I come in?
- Oh, heh.

1357
01:29:48,383 --> 01:29:50,884
A dirty business we're in, sometimes.

1358
01:29:51,052 --> 01:29:52,469
Yeah.

1359
01:29:56,057 --> 01:29:57,140
Mr. President...

1360
01:29:57,308 --> 01:30:01,520
...whatever happens, I just wanted you
to know that I think your jobs program is...

1361
01:30:01,687 --> 01:30:03,105
...a wonderful idea.

1362
01:30:06,567 --> 01:30:07,734
Thanks.

1363
01:30:07,902 --> 01:30:10,112
Not many people are gonna
pay much attention now, but....

1364
01:30:10,279 --> 01:30:11,905
[SCOFFS]

1365
01:30:12,198 --> 01:30:13,573
Thanks.

1366
01:30:19,831 --> 01:30:21,415
Uh, uh....

1367
01:30:22,583 --> 01:30:23,917
Would you like to...

1368
01:30:24,085 --> 01:30:26,294
...sit down for a minute?

1369
01:30:27,880 --> 01:30:29,339
Sure.

1370
01:30:38,266 --> 01:30:39,391
Do you ever, uh....

1371
01:30:39,559 --> 01:30:40,934
Ahem.

1372
01:30:41,102 --> 01:30:43,311
...think back to how you got started?

1373
01:30:45,398 --> 01:30:47,566
Um, heh....

1374
01:30:47,733 --> 01:30:49,734
I was a shoe salesman.

1375
01:30:50,903 --> 01:30:52,946
But not very happy about it.

1376
01:30:53,614 --> 01:30:57,284
One day, my wife says to me:

1377
01:30:57,452 --> 01:31:00,203
"Why don't you try running for office?

1378
01:31:00,371 --> 01:31:02,914
You know?
You talk about it all the time.

1379
01:31:03,082 --> 01:31:04,583
Why don't you just go do it?"

1380
01:31:04,750 --> 01:31:06,835
So I tell my boss...

1381
01:31:07,003 --> 01:31:09,588
...I have a dentist appointment...

1382
01:31:09,755 --> 01:31:13,383
...and I go down
to the Registrar of Voters...

1383
01:31:13,551 --> 01:31:15,343
...on my lunch break.

1384
01:31:16,762 --> 01:31:18,972
Next thing I know, I'm a councilman.

1385
01:31:20,057 --> 01:31:22,350
- Really?
- My wife was my campaign manager.

1386
01:31:22,518 --> 01:31:28,148
We had a budget of $2000
with advertising.

1387
01:31:28,941 --> 01:31:29,983
[VANCE CHUCKLES]

1388
01:31:30,693 --> 01:31:31,985
[VANCE SCOFFS

1389
01:31:34,739 --> 01:31:35,780
How about you?

1390
01:31:36,866 --> 01:31:38,867
- Me?
- Yeah.

1391
01:31:39,994 --> 01:31:42,078
How did you get started?

1392
01:31:44,957 --> 01:31:46,875
Kind of the same way.

1393
01:31:59,305 --> 01:32:01,431
Vice-president's a good man, isn't he?

1394
01:32:06,812 --> 01:32:08,230
Yes.

1395
01:32:10,149 --> 01:32:12,192
He's a very good man.

1396
01:32:19,367 --> 01:32:20,909
I don't want to lose you.

1397
01:32:39,011 --> 01:32:42,556
The president has requested this rare,
joint session of Congress...

1398
01:32:42,723 --> 01:32:47,018
...so he can personally answer
the allegations raised by Bob Alexander...

1399
01:32:47,186 --> 01:32:48,520
...his former chief of staff.

1400
01:32:48,688 --> 01:32:52,023
MAN [ON TV]: Frankly, it's hard to recall
the last time both houses of Congress...

1401
01:32:52,191 --> 01:32:55,527
...convened without so much of an idea
of what the president plans to say.

1402
01:32:55,695 --> 01:32:58,446
WOMAN [ON TV]: So one Would speculate
that it's about the charges...

1403
01:32:58,614 --> 01:33:00,657
...against the vice-president
and president..

1404
01:33:00,825 --> 01:33:04,953
Those rumors have been circulating
on Capitol Hill now for several weeks.

1405
01:33:06,289 --> 01:33:08,707
It's time to go. Better get inside.

1406
01:33:09,000 --> 01:33:10,584
- It's all set with Duane?
- All set.

1407
01:33:10,751 --> 01:33:11,793
Everything's here.

1408
01:33:11,961 --> 01:33:13,378
Okay, let's go.

1409
01:33:16,882 --> 01:33:18,466
Relax.

1410
01:33:19,176 --> 01:33:20,343
Right.

1411
01:33:20,511 --> 01:33:23,388
- Enjoy the moment.
- Right.

1412
01:33:28,060 --> 01:33:29,894
- Hello, Ben.
- Big day, Bob.

1413
01:33:30,062 --> 01:33:32,439
- Thanks for coming. Come on in.
- I wouldn't miss it.

1414
01:33:32,607 --> 01:33:34,816
- You know the Claghorns?
BEN: - Of course. Of course.

1415
01:33:34,984 --> 01:33:36,526
Hey, Bob, what do you think?

1416
01:33:36,694 --> 01:33:39,237
Put that away.
Let's wait till the speech first.

1417
01:33:40,990 --> 01:33:46,786
The House will be in order.

1418
01:33:50,750 --> 01:33:54,336
Mr. Speaker,
the President of the United States.

1419
01:34:28,329 --> 01:34:31,122
Thank you. Thank you.

1420
01:34:31,874 --> 01:34:32,957
Shh, shh, shh....

1421
01:34:33,125 --> 01:34:34,626
Here it comes.

1422
01:34:37,630 --> 01:34:39,255
DAVE [ON TV]:
Mr. Speaker.

1423
01:34:39,882 --> 01:34:41,633
Vice-President.

1424
01:34:42,134 --> 01:34:44,094
Members of the Congress.

1425
01:34:44,929 --> 01:34:46,721
Fellow Americans.

1426
01:34:49,392 --> 01:34:52,644
I wish I could be here today
under different circumstances.

1427
01:34:53,938 --> 01:34:58,024
There are a lot of things about this
country that we should be discussing.

1428
01:34:58,192 --> 01:35:00,777
But I realize that's not possible now.

1429
01:35:01,946 --> 01:35:06,324
As all of you know, my former chief of
staff has implicated me in a scandal...

1430
01:35:06,492 --> 01:35:09,994
...involving
the First Liberty Savings and Loan.

1431
01:35:10,162 --> 01:35:14,708
Once people start talking about a scandal,
it's hard to talk about anything else.

1432
01:35:14,875 --> 01:35:16,960
So fine, let's talk about it.

1433
01:35:18,838 --> 01:35:20,964
Bob Alexander has accused me of....

1434
01:35:21,966 --> 01:35:24,676
Let me read this to make sure I get it right.

1435
01:35:25,177 --> 01:35:27,554
"lllegally influencing
government regulators...

1436
01:35:27,722 --> 01:35:30,598
...on behalf
of major campaign contributors...

1437
01:35:30,766 --> 01:35:33,810
...interfering with an ongoing
Justice Department investigation...

1438
01:35:33,978 --> 01:35:38,356
...and violating federal election
laws in the area of campaign finance."

1439
01:35:38,524 --> 01:35:40,608
Okay, let's get right to the guts of it.

1440
01:35:41,152 --> 01:35:43,403
Each one of these charges
is absolutely true.

1441
01:35:44,655 --> 01:35:45,905
[BOB CHUCKLES]

1442
01:35:46,073 --> 01:35:48,158
Die, you pond scum.

1443
01:35:48,325 --> 01:35:51,870
I'm the president, and as they say,
the buck stops here.

1444
01:35:52,037 --> 01:35:57,375
So I take full responsibility for
every one of my illegal actions.

1445
01:35:58,669 --> 01:36:01,129
But, you see, that's not the whole story.

1446
01:36:02,465 --> 01:36:06,342
And I think each one of you
is entitled to the whole truth.

1447
01:36:07,261 --> 01:36:09,637
I have here written proof...

1448
01:36:12,433 --> 01:36:16,853
...in the form of notes, memoranda
and personal directives...

1449
01:36:17,021 --> 01:36:21,357
...proving that Bob Alexander
was also involved...

1450
01:36:21,525 --> 01:36:25,403
...in each one of these incidents,
and in most cases, planned them as well.

1451
01:36:27,823 --> 01:36:29,324
Alan.

1452
01:36:30,034 --> 01:36:35,497
Now, allegations of wrongdoing have also
been made against Vice-President Nance.

1453
01:36:35,664 --> 01:36:38,291
Now, as this evidence
will prove, at no time...

1454
01:36:38,459 --> 01:36:41,628
...and in no way was the vice-president
involved in any of this.

1455
01:36:41,796 --> 01:36:43,546
Bob just made all that up.

1456
01:36:46,258 --> 01:36:48,259
Vice-President Nance...

1457
01:36:48,928 --> 01:36:52,180
...is a good and decent public servant...

1458
01:36:52,473 --> 01:36:57,143
...and I'd like to apologize for any pain
this may have caused him or his family.

1459
01:37:00,606 --> 01:37:02,232
[SPEAKING INDISTICTLY]

1460
01:37:12,368 --> 01:37:14,410
And while we're on the subject...

1461
01:37:15,204 --> 01:37:19,082
...I'd like to apologize
to the American people.

1462
01:37:19,375 --> 01:37:21,084
You see...

1463
01:37:21,377 --> 01:37:25,505
...I forgot that I was hired
to do a job for you...

1464
01:37:25,673 --> 01:37:28,508
...and it was just a temp job at that.

1465
01:37:28,676 --> 01:37:30,635
I forgot that I had 250 million people...

1466
01:37:30,803 --> 01:37:34,681
...who were paying me to make
their lives a little bit better.

1467
01:37:34,849 --> 01:37:37,100
And I didn't live up to
my part of the bargain.

1468
01:37:38,227 --> 01:37:39,561
See....

1469
01:37:40,104 --> 01:37:43,398
I think there are certain things
you should expect from your president.

1470
01:37:45,401 --> 01:37:48,319
I had to care more about you
than I do about me.

1471
